“Romus...”

“And, for the record, I can still navigate these halls without assistance--”

“Forgive my lack of decorum. I should treat this day with the gravity it deserves."

Gradually, she drew near, her eyes conveying unexpressed sentiments.

“You of all people know what an extraordinary woman she was. Though I confess it took me a while to warm up to her."

“I remember the exact moment my feelings toward her changed.”

“It was right after the civil war broke out in Wehlen. You two were at Palas Rezna for dinner, and Lena and I absconded for tea after you and your father got into another one of your rows."

Estela Toras: “Up to that point, I was adamant th...

“Up to that point, I was adamant that Rizia should accept as few Wehzek refugees as possible. But as I spoke with your late wife about the situation, she made such a convincing case for empathy and kindness that I was literally moved to tears."

Estela Toras: “She had this way of seeing past po...
en


“She had this way of seeing past politics, straight to the heart of the matter. The very next day, I persuaded Valero to open our borders."

“Quite the keepsake.”

"You were her mother-in-law. There's always some friction in that relationship."

"How do you know she was extraordinary? You two barely spoke."

"I didn't know you felt that way about her."

"How very thoughtful."

“A love letter from your father -- the first one he ever wrote. And I thought it only fitting to give it back.”

My mother left the room, and I followed behind.

We made our way down the great hall, past the resting places of the great leaders and some not-so-great who came before me.

It wasn’t long before the light from the eternal flame, a single torch placed at the late king’s sarcophagus symbolizing a monarch’s enduring reign, guided us the rest of the way.

Narrator: As we neared, my mother’s pace slow...

As we neared, my mother’s pace slowed as if an overwhelming wave of memories pressed upon her.

The flame's flickering glow cast dancing shadows on the path.

We stopped just before we reached my father’s stone encasing.

Estela Toras: “There you are...”
en


“There you are...”

en


We both fell silent.

Estela Toras: “If you don’t mind, I’d like to say...

“If you don’t mind, I’d like to say a few words to your father.”

en


“Please, by all means.”

Estela Toras: “Val... I feel the need to speak to...

“Val... I feel the need to speak to you, even though you've departed. For two decades, we walked different paths, our views often conflicting, and our words sometimes harsh."

LineNo: 13639647,

Estela Toras: Despite the clashes, there was an...
en


"Despite the clashes, there was an enduring love that started years ago when our hearts first connected. It survived storms and endured the worst of our disagreements."

LineNo: 13639749,

Estela Toras: Our journey had its cruelties, but...
en


"Our journey had its cruelties, but it never diminished the warmth your presence brought. As I reflect, I realize that love was our constant, despite its complexities."

LineNo: 13639867,

Estela Toras: So, in this space between the livi...
en


"So, in this space between the living and the departed, I speak these final words. My reserved heart lays bare the truth—I loved you then, I love you now."

LineNo: 13639969,

Narrator: She presented the love letter to th...
en


She presented the love letter to the flame, watching as it intensified, consuming the paper until it vanished.

LineNo: 13640071,

Estela Toras: “May it rest with him, carrying the...
en


“May it rest with him, carrying the memories of a cherished connection and the legacy he left behind."

LineNo: 13640197,

Player_Romus: “Legacy... I doubt history will be...
en


“Legacy... I doubt history will be very kind.”

LineNo: 13640299,

Estela Toras: “I’m not speaking of his actions on...
en


“I’m not speaking of his actions on the throne. His legacy is you.”

LineNo: 13640417,

Player_Romus: “A heavy burden to bear -- a name f...
en


“A heavy burden to bear -- a name forever stained by the judgments of time.”

Estela Toras: “Legacies are shaped by more than j...
en


“Legacies are shaped by more than just deeds. What you make of the name matters just as much.”

LineNo: 13640645,

en


“I can't escape the shadows of his choices, no matter what path I forge.”

LineNo: 13640747,

en


"Maybe not, but you can cast new shadows that speak of redemption and resilience."

Player_Romus: “Redemption? I'm not sure that's a...
en


“Redemption? I'm not sure that's a luxury afforded to our family name.”

Estela Toras: “You have the power to redefine wha...
en


“You have the power to redefine what it means to bear that name. The future is still yours to shape.”

Estela Toras: “Sometimes, the most profound respo...
en


“Sometimes, the most profound responsibilities are the ones we inherit, not by choice, but by destiny.”

Player_Romus: “Destiny or not, I'll strive to lea...
en


“Destiny or not, I'll strive to leave a legacy that stands apart from the mistakes of my father."

LineNo: 13641297,

Player_Romus: “My triumph over Pales will rectify...
en


“My triumph over Pales will rectify his failure.”

Estela Toras: “Or be your undoing, just like him....
en


“Or be your undoing, just like him. He was so hell-bent on achieving victory at any cost that it consumed him, as I fear it may be consuming you.”

Narrator: I began pacing around the hall.
en


I began pacing around the hall.

en


“You know nothing.”

“So sure of yourself. I'll tell you what I do know... ”

en


“I know that my son is determined to embark on some military expedition when his attention should be dedicated to the rightful restoration of Zille.”

en


“I know that the very foundations of the monarchy have been put at risk through such actions.”

Player_Romus: “Risks? Okay, if we’re going to go...

“Risks? Okay, if we’re going to go there, tell me... how do you foresee the public responding if it's uncovered that Her Majesty Queen Estela clandestinely adheres to Dastnurity?”

LineNo: 13642239,

Narrator: The color drained from her face, le...
en


The color drained from her face, leaving her visibly pale.

en


“I don’t know what you’re talking about.”

“Well, I have first-hand accounts that will say otherwise.”

“It’s called faith for a reason. It's not something you casually discard, like shedding clothes for a different outfit.”

“If you’re looking for an apology, you can forget it. I will not renounce my beliefs to appease anyone's expectations.”

en


“And I’ll be damned if you think otherwise!”

The lingering sound of her final words reverberated throughout the chamber.

Narrator: She scoffed.
en


She scoffed.

en


“If only he could see you now... what he would think...”

Player_Romus: “Fine. I’ll go. But understand this...
en


“Fine. I’ll go. But understand this... when it comes to legacy, I forge my own destiny. I refuse to be shackled by the wishes and desires of a rotting corpse. And I don’t give a fuck about what my father would think of me.”

Narrator: I don’t remember leaving the mausol...

Player_Romus: Not at this moment, Mother. I have...

"Not at this moment, Mother. I have more pressing matters to attend to."

Player_Romus: I'll give you some privacy.
en


"I'll give you some privacy."

LineNo: 13644641,

Player_Romus: I find comfort in knowing that his...
en


"I find comfort in knowing that his legacy lives on, but it doesn't change the pain of his absence."

"For better or worse, his legacy will live on."

en


"I'll ensure the name stands strong, even if it means shouldering the weight alone."

en


"My actions speak louder than any family name. I'll forge my path, legacy be damned."

en


"I'm aware of the impact a name can have. My actions will reflect the values I hold and the path I choose for our family. Just as God intended."

Player_Romus: Perhaps. But I'll paint a legacy t...

"Perhaps. But I'll paint a legacy that transcends any failings or shortcomings of the past."

LineNo: 13645763,

Player_Romus: I'm aware of the impact a name can...
en


"I'm aware of the impact a name can have. My actions will reflect the values I hold and the path I choose for our family."

"Indeed they are. Like divine threads in a grand design, guiding us toward a purpose beyond our choosing, much like Father."

LineNo: 13646069,

Player_Romus: Inheritances come in many forms. I...
en


"Inheritances come in many forms. I'll embrace whatever responsibilities destiny throws at me, be it triumphs or defeats, much like my father."

Player_Romus: My victory over Pales will honor h...
en


"My victory over Pales will honor his memory by finishing what he started."

"God willing, my victory over Pales will honor his memory by finishing what he started."

"You possess the skill to foresee the future now? You don't know what you're talking about."

Player_Romus: I too hear whispers, whispers that...

Player_Romus: Risk... this coming from the perso...

"Risk... this coming from the person who's been secretly practicing a Dastnurity right under my nose... or so the rumors say."

"Don't lie to me! Do you take me for a fool? I know all about it."

en


"Oh, quit playing dumb. You know very well what I'm saying is true."

LineNo: 13647089,

Player_Romus: Come on, Mother. I know all about...
en


"Come on, Mother. I know all about it."

Player_Romus: Look, I honestly don't care what y...

"Look, I honestly don't care what you believe. I just wish you'd been forthright about it."

Player_Romus: Well, it goes without saying that...
en


"Well, it goes without saying that you've shattered my trust."

"So it is true... Well, I hope in due time I can learn to overlook this deception. Can't say I'm not disappointed."

LineNo: 13647497,

Player_Romus: Fine, I'll go. But let me be perfe...
en


"Fine, I'll go. But let me be perfectly clear... I couldn't care less about Father's legacy or what he would think of me. But I am resolute in rectifying his errors by achieving what he failed to do -- the first thing being, to reclaim Pales for Rizia. My victory will be mine and mine alone."

LineNo: 13647599,

Player_Romus: Alright, I'll go. Contrary to your...
en


"Alright, I'll go. Contrary to your assumptions, you should know that I intend to uphold Father's legacy with the same dedication as Rizia's. That's why I am steadfast in rejuvenating this nation and paying tribute to his memory, in accordance with his wishes, and do right by him."

Player_Romus: Very well, I'll go. Despite what y...
en


"Very well, I'll go. Despite what you might think, I aim to preserve Father's legacy and do right by him. As a tribute to his memory, I vow to fulfill what he started by reclaiming Pales. His vision for the kingdom will become our reality."

LineNo: 13647803,

Estela Toras: Farewell, until we meet where love...
en


"Farewell, until we meet where love knows no bounds."

LineNo: 13647905,

Estela Toras: The years etched lines on our face...
en


"The years etched lines on our faces, but they also deepened my affection for you. Through triumphs and tribulations, you were my confidante, my partner, my solace."

LineNo: 13648007,

Estela Toras: Tonight, standing by your resting...
en


"Tonight, standing by your resting place, I want you to know that my heart bears no bitterness. Instead, it holds the echoes of laughter, shared moments, and a touch that transcends words."

LineNo: 13648589,

Narrator: Vina, of course, was by my side. In...
en


Vina, of course, was by my side. In fact, ever since her return from Pales, she had remained virtually tethered to my hip. She was holding a bouquet.

LineNo: 13649343,

Narrator: I gave her some space to allow for...
en


I gave her some space to allow for a moment between the two of them. She spoke to him in a hushed whisper, for much longer than I expected.

LineNo: 13649445,

Narrator: Whatever she had to say was evident...
en


Whatever she had to say was evidently meaningful, perhaps something she had been holding back, especially considering their strained relationship for most of his life.

Narrator: When she was finished, she took out...
en


When she was finished, she took out the love letter and placed it on the lid of the sarcophagus. I took this as my cue to return.

Player_Romus: I do mind, actually. You could hav...
en


"I do mind, actually. You could have said what you needed to say within the past four years."

Narrator: I stepped away, granting her some s...
en


I stepped away, granting her some space in an attempt to create a moment between the two of them.

en


"Fine. If that's the way you feel about it, then I'll just do it another time."

en


We stood in silence. The atmosphere, full of unsaid thoughts, held us captive in a shared pause.

Narrator: She spoke to him in a hushed whispe...
en


She spoke to him in a hushed whisper, prolonging the conversation far longer than I anticipated.

Narrator: Whatever she had to say was evident...
en

"Oh, spare me your sentimental nonsense. I have more pressing matters to worry about."

LineNo: 13650963,

"I don't have the patience for your melodramatic indulgence. Find your closure elsewhere."

en


"My apologies. It's been a long day."

Player_Romus: Playing the victim card as usual...
en


"Playing the victim card as usual..."

LineNo: 13651269,

en


"Again, you've had four years to do that, as I'm sure you'll have another four years, and another, and another..."

en


"If you insist on continuing down such a path, cruelty may very well define your legacy."

en


"Like the stone-cold walls of this mausoleum, my legacy shall stand firm, indifferent to sentimentality or familial pleas.”

en


"What do you know of legacy?"

"I take it this is where you tell me about the importance of legacy and the footprints I leave behind in the sands of history."

en


"Please, enlighten me."
